&lt;p&gt;Translation by Bhikkhu Sujato.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="11-subhūti"&gt;1.1 Subhūti&lt;a class="anchor" href="#11-subh%c5%abti"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My little hut is roofed and pleasant,&lt;br&gt;
Sheltered from the wind:&lt;br&gt;
So rain, sky, as you please!&lt;br&gt;
My mind is serene and freed,&lt;br&gt;
I practice whole-heartedly: so rain, sky!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="12-mahākoṭṭhika"&gt;1.2 Mahākoṭṭhika&lt;a class="anchor" href="#12-mah%c4%81ko%e1%b9%ad%e1%b9%adhika"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Calm and quiet,
Wise in counsel and steady;
Shaking off bad qualities,
As the wind shakes leaves off a tree.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="13-kaṅkhārevata"&gt;1.3 Kaṅkhārevata&lt;a class="anchor" href="#13-ka%e1%b9%85kh%c4%81revata"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;See this wisdom of the Tathāgatas!
Like a fire blazing in the night,
Giving light, giving vision,
Dispelling the doubt of those who’ve come here.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>